File: Former Springbok wing James Small died last week from a heart attack. JOHANNESBURG - Mourners will gather at the Wanderers Rugby club on Thursday afternoon for the funeral of James Small.
The former Springbok wing died last week from a heart attack. READ: 'Beast' puts body and soul on line for World Cup The service will take place in a restricted area but will broadcast live to a public area. No accreditation is needed for the funeral.